 has been chosen as one of the  best employers in america by business insider criticismedit on february   duke energy said that it expects to settle a federal criminal probe into a  north carolina coal ash spill for  million following a february   coal ash spill which was the thirdlargest of its kind in us history the us attorneys office opened a grand jury investigation into duke energy and north carolina regulators in the administration of governor pat mccrory mccrory had been an employee of duke energy for  years and critics have said his administration intervened on dukes behalf to settle lawsuits over environmental violations the us attorney subpoenaed over  officials of the mccrory administration and sought records of investments cash or other items of value from duke to regulators on february   greenpeace launched a campaign in which phil radford called on duke energy to not renew a single new contract for mountaintop removal coal deliver at least a third of dukes energy from renewable sources by  and quit coal altogether by  in may  university student activists launched a divestment campaign against duke energy and other coal plant operators in july  duke energy was criticized for paying former progress energy ceo bill johnson  million in compensation including  million severance for essentially  minutes on the job as duke ceo on july  new ceo jim rogers spoke before the nc utilities commission explaining the reason for johnsons dismissal as loss of confidence he also mentioned an autocratic style though some former progress directors disagreed in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized duke energy for spending  million on lobbying and not paying any taxes during  through  and receiving  million in tax rebates despite making a profit of  billion and increasing executive pay by  to  million in  for its top  executives the company became the object of protest for its close relationship to the democratic party and its funding for the  democratic national convention in  duke energy was awarded the ig nobel prize in economics for adapting the mathematical concept of imaginary numbers for use in the business world in september  the  billion government pension fund of norway excluded duke and  of its subsidiaries citing risk of severe environmental damage taxesedit duke energy office in raleigh nc duke energy owns the crystal river energy complex in rural citrus county florida which includes the nowclosed crystal river  nuclear power plant and four fossilfuel power stations using coal in late  duke paid  million of their  property tax bill of  million and filed suit against the county claiming the assessment was too high duke power owns  acres  hectares of land and improvements assessed at over  billion constituting more than a quarter of the county tax base citrus county property appraiser geoff greene commented given the complexity history and dispute over the last years assessment of duke energys property an independent appraisal team was needed and tasked to arrive at a fair and just value with the financial assistance from the board of county commissioners and the school board greene hired two independent appraisal firms at a cost of  after five months of inspection documentation and crunching numbers the outside appraisal concluded that the county assessment was incorrect at  billion it should have been  billion based on that figure duke owed the remaining  million for  and  taxes should be  million greene stated there were a lot of unreported and underreported items see alsoedit north carolina portal companies portal energy portal  atlantic power outage harlan county usa— academy awardwinning documentary film covering the efforts of  coal miners on strike against the duke power company in harlan county kentucky in  fixed bill referencesedit  a b c d duke energy  annual report form k filing date feb   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved april     duke energy  annual report form k filing date feb   pdf