enpeace launched a campaign in which phil radford called on duke energy to not renew a single new contract for mountaintop removal coal deliver at least a third of dukes energy from renewable sources by  and quit coal altogether by  in may  university student activists launched a divestment campaign against duke energy and other coal plant operators in july  duke energy was criticized for paying former progress energy ceo bill johnson  million in compensation including  million severance for essentially  minutes on the job as duke ceo on july  new ceo jim rogers spoke before the nc utilities commission explaining the reason for johnsons dismissal as loss of confidence he also mentioned an autocratic style though some former progress directors disagreed in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized duke energy for spending  million on lobbying and not paying any taxes during  through  and receiving  million in tax rebates despite making a profit of  billion and increasing executive pay by  to  million in  for its top  executives the company became the object of protest for its close relationship to the democratic party and its funding for the  democratic national convention in  duke energy was awarded the ig nobel prize in economics for adapting the mathematical concept of imaginary numbers for use in the business world in september  the  billion government pension fund of norway excluded duke and  of its subsidiaries citing risk of severe environmental damage taxesedit duke energy office in raleigh nc duke energy owns the crystal river energy complex in rural citrus county florida which includes the nowclosed crystal river  nuclear power plant and four fossilfuel power stations using coal in late  duke paid  million of their  property tax bill of  million and filed suit against the county claiming the assessment was too high duke power owns  acres  hectares of land and improvements assessed at over  billion constituting more than a quarter of 