 its kind in us history the us attorneys office opened a grand jury investigation into duke energy and north carolina regulators in the administration of governor pat mccrory mccrory had been an employee of duke energy for  years and critics have said his administration intervened on dukes behalf to settle lawsuits over environmental violations the us attorney subpoenaed over  officials of the mccrory administration and sought records of investments cash or other items of value from duke to regulators on february   greenpeace launched a campaign in which phil radford called on duke energy to not renew a single new contract for mountaintop removal coal deliver at least a third of dukes energy from renewable sources by  and quit coal altogether by  in may  university student activists launched a divestment campaign against duke energy and other coal plant operators in july  duke energy was criticized for paying former progress energy ceo bill johnson  million in compensation including  million severance for essentially  minutes on the job as duke ceo on july  new ceo jim rogers spoke before the nc utilities commission explaining the reason for johnsons dismissal as loss of confidence he also mentioned an autocratic style though some former progress directors disagreed in december  the nonpartisan organization public campaign criticized duke energy for spending  million on lobbying and not paying any taxes during  through  and receiving  million in tax rebates despite making a profit of  billion and increasing executive pay by  to  million in  for its top  executives the company became the object of protest for its close relationship to the democratic party and its funding for the  democratic national convention in  duke energy was awarded the ig nobel prize in economics for adapting the mathematical concept of imaginary numbers for use in the business world in september  the  billion government pension fund of norway excluded duke and  of its subsidiaries citing risk 